net.akami.mask.core

Interface MaskOperator<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - potential required additional data
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MaskDerivativeCalculator, MaskImageCalculator, MaskReducer

    public interface MaskOperator<E>
    A specific operation taking an input, sorting out an output.

    Available operators :

  • MaskReducer, a simple layer for the reducing tree system. It will soon replace the ReducerFactory class.
  • MaskDerivativeCalculator, providing support for derivatives
  • MaskImageCalculator, calculating images with a given function. 
    

 Note that the Mask class will be replaced by the Expression class in the future.

      Method Detail
      






        

      • 

        compute
        

        void compute(Mask in,
             Mask out,
             E extraData,
             MaskContext context)
        

        Computes a result from the given in parameter, writing the result into the mutable out parameter,
 using the extra data required. Although some of the operators just need a single input being the in Mask,
 most of them need extra information that cannot be taken out of the initial Mask, such as which char corresponds to
 the variable (non-constant) for the derivatives calculator, or which variables should be replaced by which values
 for the images calculator.
        

        

        Parameters:
        

        in - the Mask which will be used as the basis to compute the result
        

        out - the Mask which will be used as the container for the computed result
        

        extraData - potential extra data required by the operator for each calculation
        

        context - the environment for the calculations. See MaskContext for further information
